    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-16T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-16T19:00:00-05:00" n="380"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.00/4539: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRS1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-16T20:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 16, 1919, 8 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My May 15th, 6 p.m. President directs me to request that you particularly inquire
                    as to the kind of men and influences surrounding <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1"
                        >Kolchak</persName> and ask whether in your opinion <persName
                        corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> is strong enough and liberal enough to
                    control them in the right direction.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
